<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36089c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36089c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36089c"> 89(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> stripped into his shirt</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;And then the court was called, and the appellant or plaintiff was brought in before the face of the court, being <mark>stripped into his shirt</mark>, having only his sword and target (which were the weapons appointed); and when he had done his reverence and duty to the lord justices and to the court, he was brought to a stool set in the one of the ends within the lists, and there sat.&rdquo; <font color="green">[Hooker]</font> <small> Samuel A. Ossory Fitzpatrick, <a name="SAOF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SAOF"><cite title="source">Dublin: A Historical and Topographical Account of the City</cite></a> (1907) 75</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
